Package: lm-sensors-source
Section: misc
Architecture: all
Depends: i2c-source (>= 1:2.9.0), debhelper (>= 4.0), module-assistant, bison, flex | flex-old
Description: kernel drivers to read temperature/voltage/fan sensors (source)
 Lm-sensors is a hardware health monitoring package for Linux. It allows you
 to access information from temperature, voltage, and fan speed sensors. It
 works with most newer systems.
 .
 This package contains the source for kernel modules that are necessary to
 access the data. You will also need to install the i2c-source package and
 build modules from that.
 .
 The 2.4 kernel sources must be installed to compile these modules. This
 package won't build modules for 2.6 kernels. Instead use the modules that
 are already in the kernel tree.
 .
  Homepage: http://www.lm-sensors.nu
